**Internal factions of the SPD**

Overall dissent: [+ dissent_percent : dissent +]

**Left**

The left wing of Zentrum is led by Joseph Wirth. They support cooperation with the SPD and are determined defenders of the republic. They also support appeals to the working class though they are opposed to becoming an interdenominational peoples party. [? if not hess_dead: They are dominant in Prussia under the leadership of Joseph Hess.]

Strength: [+ left_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ left_dissent : dissent +]

**Centrists**

The centrists in Zentrum generally support defending democracy and maintaining the party status quo. They are open to coalitions with both the SPD and DNVP. 

Strength: [+ center_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ center_dissent : dissent +]

**Clericals**

Given our role as a tradititionally catholic party, we have close ties with the catholic church and the Pope. This has enabled the church to gain some influence within the party while also helping to mediate between the different factions. 

Strength: [+ clerical_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ clerical_dissent : dissent +]

**Christians*

The christians, or christian democrats are centered around Adam Stegerwald and his 1920 Essen Program. They believe in a interdenominational, big tent albiet somewhat right wing Christian People's Party. This makes them an outlier within the party though they are still commited to the republic. 

Strength: [+ christian_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ christian_dissent : dissent +]

@neorevisionists
go-to: menu

**Right**

The right wing of Zentrum generally opposes the socialists above all else and support tacking to the right. They are skeptical of democracy and some even long for the days of the Kaiserreich. The BVP is also the most alligned with this group. 

Strength: [+ right_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ right_dissent : dissent +]


